sec.p:
Format for diagnosis and description of the new species follow those of Lynch and Duellman (1997). For systematic of Craugastoridae we follow Hedges et al. (2008), Pyron and Wiens (2011), and Padial et al. (2014). Specimens collected were sacrificed with a 20% benzocaine solution and fixed in 10% formalin, then stored in 70% ethanol and deposited in the herpetological collection at
Centro de Ornitologia y Biodiversidad (CORBIDI). The following variables were taken as described in Duellman and Lehr (2009) and were measured to the nearest 0.1 mm with digital calipers under a stereoscope:
snout–vent length (SVL);
eye–nostril distance (EN);
head length (HL);
head width (HW);
interorbital distance (IOD);
internarial distance (IND);
tibia length (TL);
foot length (FL);
eye diameter (ED);
upper eyelid width (EW).
